Background: Neurofibromatosis 2 (NF2) is a rare autosomal dominant disorder (prevalence 1:37.000) associated with changes in tumor suppressor genes. Intraocular manifestations have been reported as subcapsular cataract, retinal hamartomas, epiretinal membranes, keratopathy in facial palsy, and tumors of the nerves I-V are typical ocular manifestations of NF2.  
